    "solution": "<p>Consider the structure of $\\mathrm{HNO}_3$</p>\n<p><img alt=\"JEE Main 2026 (Online) 22nd January Morning Shift Chemistry - Chemical Bonding &amp; Molecular Structure Question 19 English Explanation\" src=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/6y3zli1mlg75jbz/c1c5cb0a-4055-4563-b0ad-747aa9bdeccf/76d47af0-0646-11f1-aa69-f351c2bbeb5d/file-6y3zli1mlg75jc0.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/6y3zli1mlg75jbz/c1c5cb0a-4055-4563-b0ad-747aa9bdeccf/76d47af0-0646-11f1-aa69-f351c2bbeb5d/file-6y3zli1mlg75jc0.png\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0 auto;max-height:40vh;vertical-align:baseline\"></p>\n<p>$\\begin{aligned} &amp; 1:-0 \\\\ &amp; 2:-(+1) \\\\ &amp; 3:-0 \\\\ &amp; 4:-(-1) \\\\ &amp; \\text { Formal charge }=\\text { valence } \\mathrm{e} \\text { 's }- \\text { non bonding e's } - (\\frac{\\text { bonding electrons }}{2})\\end{aligned}$</p>",
    "__v": 0,
    "title": "JEE Main 2026 (Online) 22nd January Morning Shift"
