    "solution": "<p><img alt=\"JEE Main 2026 (Online) 6th April Morning Shift Chemistry - Chemical Bonding &amp; Molecular Structure Question 3 English Explanation 1\" src=\"https://app-content.fly-assets.uk/fly/@width/image/jaoe38c1mobqe60p/546cd299-5f09-429f-bbd4-dcdf5e544019/6f2bee90-3f36-11f1-8907-9d59f06ca3d8/file-jaoe38c1mobqe60q.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.fly-assets.uk/image/jaoe38c1mobqe60p/546cd299-5f09-429f-bbd4-dcdf5e544019/6f2bee90-3f36-11f1-8907-9d59f06ca3d8/file-jaoe38c1mobqe60q.png\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0 auto;max-height:40vh;vertical-align:baseline\"></p>\n<p><img alt=\"JEE Main 2026 (Online) 6th April Morning Shift Chemistry - Chemical Bonding &amp; Molecular Structure Question 3 English Explanation 2\" src=\"https://app-content.fly-assets.uk/fly/@width/image/jaoe38c1mobqe6t4/af1f45a5-d664-4e4b-b967-1586fc922434/6fc80780-3f36-11f1-8907-9d59f06ca3d8/file-jaoe38c1mobqe6t5.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.fly-assets.uk/image/jaoe38c1mobqe6t4/af1f45a5-d664-4e4b-b967-1586fc922434/6fc80780-3f36-11f1-8907-9d59f06ca3d8/file-jaoe38c1mobqe6t5.png\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0 auto;max-height:40vh;vertical-align:baseline\"></p>\n<p><img alt=\"JEE Main 2026 (Online) 6th April Morning Shift Chemistry - Chemical Bonding &amp; Molecular Structure Question 3 English Explanation 3\" src=\"https://app-content.fly-assets.uk/fly/@width/image/jaoe38c1mobqe792/a0558571-04b8-46c8-bb34-22a09828eb5f/701f9d60-3f36-11f1-8907-9d59f06ca3d8/file-jaoe38c1mobqe793.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.fly-assets.uk/image/jaoe38c1mobqe792/a0558571-04b8-46c8-bb34-22a09828eb5f/701f9d60-3f36-11f1-8907-9d59f06ca3d8/file-jaoe38c1mobqe793.png\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0 auto;max-height:40vh;vertical-align:baseline\"></p>\n<p><img alt=\"JEE Main 2026 (Online) 6th April Morning Shift Chemistry - Chemical Bonding &amp; Molecular Structure Question 3 English Explanation 4\" src=\"https://app-content.fly-assets.uk/fly/@width/image/jaoe38c1mobqe7t0/a09b76bd-deff-4799-97b0-42404863d63b/708d2c40-3f36-11f1-8907-9d59f06ca3d8/file-jaoe38c1mobqe7t1.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.fly-assets.uk/image/jaoe38c1mobqe7t0/a09b76bd-deff-4799-97b0-42404863d63b/708d2c40-3f36-11f1-8907-9d59f06ca3d8/file-jaoe38c1mobqe7t1.png\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0 auto;max-height:40vh;vertical-align:baseline\"></p>\n<p>$$ \\begin{aligned}(E)\\,\\, &amp; \\operatorname{MnO4}^{-2}=7+4 \\times 2+2=4+10=17 e^{-} \\\\ &amp; \\operatorname{CrO4} ^{-2}=6+4 \\times 2+2=6+10=16 e^{-} \\end{aligned} $$</p>\n<p>since $e^{-}$count is notequal, leawis dot structure will be different.</p>",
