    "solution": "<p>NO$_2^-$ ion</p>\n<p><img src=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/jaoe38c1m7pone43/63efa871-ce74-4530-9366-de596850d6b8/e9193830-f652-11ef-a1b4-cfcc45a12e4c/file-jaoe38c1m7pone44.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/jaoe38c1m7pone43/63efa871-ce74-4530-9366-de596850d6b8/e9193830-f652-11ef-a1b4-cfcc45a12e4c/file-jaoe38c1m7pone44.png\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0 auto;max-height:40vh;vertical-align:baseline\" alt=\"JEE Main 2025 (Online) 29th January Evening Shift Chemistry - Chemical Bonding &amp; Molecular Structure Question 43 English Explanation\"></p>\n<p>Structure (Lewis Structure)</p>\n<p>Nitrogen (N) has 2 non-bonding electrons. The total valence electrons of N is 5. Out of 5, 3 electrons are bonding electrons and 2 electrons are non-bonding electrons.</p>\n<p>Double bonded oxygen has 4 non-bonding electrons. Oxygen valence electrons : 6</p>\n<p>Out of 6, 2 are bonding electrons are 4 are non-bonding electrons.</p>\n<p>Negatively charged oxygen has 6 non-bonding electrons. The negative charge is due to the extra electron present. So, the total number of non-bonded electrons present in NO$_2^-$ ion based on Lewis theory is</p>\n<p>$$2(of\\,N) + 4(of\\,O) + 6(of\\,{O^ - })$$</p>\n<p>$$ = 2 + 4 + 6 = 12$$</p>",
    "__v": 0,
    "title": "JEE Main 2025 (Online) 29th January Evening Shift"
  },
