    "solution": "<p>Statement - I :</p>\n<p><img src=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/jaoe38c1m9urww2l/91fb16b8-1925-42dd-9852-1c6fb5f4af6e/06a540d0-20b8-11f0-a8f0-f9bcac944d27/file-jaoe38c1m9urww2m.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/jaoe38c1m9urww2l/91fb16b8-1925-42dd-9852-1c6fb5f4af6e/06a540d0-20b8-11f0-a8f0-f9bcac944d27/file-jaoe38c1m9urww2m.png\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0 auto;max-height:40vh;vertical-align:baseline\" alt=\"JEE Main 2025 (Online) 4th April Morning Shift Chemistry - Chemical Bonding &amp; Molecular Structure Question 26 English Explanation 1\"></p>\n<p>$$\\mu=\\mathrm{q} \\times \\mathrm{d}$$</p>\n<p>More charges and more distance between charges than other compound so more dipole moment.</p>\n<p>Statement-I is true.</p>\n<p>Statement-II :</p>\n<p><img src=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/jaoe38c1m9ury2vy/1dc956e6-94d6-47be-8d5d-4c9cb515a9bf/27b833e0-20b8-11f0-a8f0-f9bcac944d27/file-jaoe38c1m9ury2vz.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/jaoe38c1m9ury2vy/1dc956e6-94d6-47be-8d5d-4c9cb515a9bf/27b833e0-20b8-11f0-a8f0-f9bcac944d27/file-jaoe38c1m9ury2vz.png\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0 auto;max-height:40vh;vertical-align:baseline\" alt=\"JEE Main 2025 (Online) 4th April Morning Shift Chemistry - Chemical Bonding &amp; Molecular Structure Question 26 English Explanation 2\"></p>\n<p>$\\mathrm{C}_1-\\mathrm{C}_2$ bond has partial double bond character that means lesser bond length than $C_1-C_2$ bond of other compound.</p>\n<p>Statement-II is false.</p>",
    "__v": 0,
